---
// Internal meeting checklist — not linked anywhere, noindex, excluded from sitemap.
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow">
<title>WCCP Meeting — 13 May 2026, 1:30pm</title>
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  :root {
    --navy: #131E44; --navy-mid: #3a5cb5; --yellow: #f5c13b;
    --red: #c0392b; --amber: #e67e22; --green: #27ae60;
    --bone: #f7f5f0; --cast: #6b7280; --border: #d1d5db;
  }
  body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5; background: var(--bone); color: var(--navy); padding: 24px 16px 60px; }
  .page { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .header { background: var(--navy); color: white; border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px 28px; margin-bottom: 20px; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; gap: 20px; }
  .header-left h1 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.3px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .header-left h1 span { color: var(--yellow); }
  .header-left p { margin-top: 6px; font-size: 13px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6); }
  .header-right { text-align: right; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .header-right .time { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--yellow); line-height: 1; }
  .header-right .date { font-size: 12px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); margin-top: 4px; }
  .must-banner { background: var(--red); color: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 13px; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px; }
  .must-banner .icon { font-size: 18px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .must-banner ul { margin: 6px 0 0 20px; font-weight: 500; font-size: 13px; }
  .must-banner ul li { margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .section { background: white; border-radius: 10px; border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 16px; overflow: hidden; }
  .section-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; padding: 13px 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .section-header .badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; width: 22px; height: 22px; border-radius: 50%; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 800; flex-shrink: 0; color: white; }
  .badge-red { background: var(--red); } .badge-amber { background: var(--amber); } .badge-green { background: var(--green); } .badge-navy { background: var(--navy-mid); }
  .section-header h2 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; flex: 1; }
  .section-header .count { font-size: 11px; color: var(--cast); font-weight: 500; }
  .items { padding: 6px 0; }
  .item { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 20px 1fr auto; align-items: start; gap: 8px; padding: 9px 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid #f3f4f6; transition: background 0.15s; }
  .item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .item:hover { background: #fafafa; }
  .item.done { opacity: 0.45; }
  .item.done .label { text-decoration: line-through; }
  .item input[type="checkbox"] { width: 16px; height: 16px; accent-color: var(--navy); cursor: pointer; margin-top: 2px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .item .label { font-weight: 600; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--navy); line-height: 1.3; }
  .item .sub { font-size: 12px; color: var(--cast); margin-top: 2px; line-height: 1.4; }
  .item .tag { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 4px; white-space: nowrap; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
  .tag-r { background: #fde8e8; color: var(--red); } .tag-a { background: #fef3cd; color: #92400e; }
  .tag-g { background: #d1fae5; color: #065f46; } .tag-b { background: #dbeafe; color: #1e40af; }
  .tag-p { background: #ede9fe; color: #5b21b6; }
  .how-toggle { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px; margin-top: 5px; font-size: 11.5px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy-mid); cursor: pointer; background: none; border: none; padding: 0; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .how-toggle:hover { color: var(--navy); }
  .how-block { display: none; margin-top: 8px; background: #f0f4ff; border-left: 3px solid var(--navy-mid); border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0; padding: 10px 12px; }
  .how-block.open { display: block; }
  .how-block ol { margin: 0 0 0 16px; padding: 0; }
  .how-block ol li { font-size: 12px; color: #1e3a8a; line-height: 1.55; margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .how-block ol li strong { font-weight: 700; }
  .how-block .how-note { font-size: 11.5px; color: #374151; margin-top: 6px; font-style: italic; }
  .notes-section { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 16px; overflow: hidden; }
  .notes-header { padding: 13px 18px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy); }
  .notes-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0; }
  .notes-col { padding: 14px 18px; }
  .notes-col:first-child { border-right: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .notes-col h3 { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.07em; color: var(--cast); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .notes-col textarea { width: 100%; min-height: 100px; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; padding: 8px 10px; font-family: inherit; font-size: 13px; color: var(--navy); resize: vertical; background: #fafafa; }
  .notes-col textarea:focus { outline: 2px solid var(--navy-mid); background: white; }
  .footer { text-align: center; font-size: 11px; color: var(--cast); margin-top: 24px; }
  .progress-bar { background: #e5e7eb; border-radius: 4px; height: 6px; margin: 12px 18px 14px; overflow: hidden; }
  .progress-fill { height: 100%; background: var(--green); border-radius: 4px; width: 0%; transition: width 0.3s; }
  .progress-label { text-align: right; font-size: 11px; color: var(--cast); padding: 0 18px 8px; }
  .sub-heading { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--cast); padding: 10px 18px 6px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .sub-heading:first-of-type { border-top: none; }
  @media print {
    body { background: white; padding: 0; font-size: 12px; }
    .header { border-radius: 0; }
    .section, .notes-section { break-inside: avoid; }
    textarea { border: 1px solid #ccc !important; background: white !important; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page">

  <div class="header">
    <div class="header-left">
      <h1>WCCP Meeting — <span>Everything we need</span></h1>
      <p>Kim Rumsam · Holsworthy yard · Matt + Rebecca attending</p>
      <p style="margin-top:10px; font-size:12px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);">
        🔴 Critical — must leave with today &nbsp;·&nbsp; 🟡 Hand over this week &nbsp;·&nbsp; 🟢 During build (weeks 2–6)
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="header-right">
      <div class="time">1:30pm</div>
      <div class="date">Tuesday 13 May 2026</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="must-banner">
    <span class="icon">🚨</span>
    <div>
      DO NOT LEAVE WITHOUT:
      <ul>
        <li>GA4 + Search Console + Google Business Profile access added (email: leonardbmillard@gmail.com)</li>
        <li>WordPress / current site admin login</li>
        <li>Bluehost / JustHost cPanel login from Kim</li>
        <li>Logo vector files (.ai / .eps / .svg) on USB or shared drive link</li>
        <li>All existing photos on USB or Drive link — everything they own</li>
        <li>Photo shoot date locked in the diary</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 1 -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="badge badge-red">1</span>
      <h2>Digital access — add leonardbmillard@gmail.com as admin/owner</h2>
      <span class="count">7 items</span>
    </div>
    <div class="items" id="s1">
      <div class="item">
        <input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)">
        <div class="body">
          <div class="label">Google Analytics 4 (GA4)</div>
          <div class="sub">This is the tool that shows how many people visit your website and what they do on it. We need to see your data so we can measure whether the new site is working.</div>
          <button class="how-toggle" onclick="toggleHow(this)">▶ How to do this</button>
          <div class="how-block">
            <ol>
              <li>On Kim's computer, go to <strong>analytics.google.com</strong> and sign in with the Google account linked to WCCP.</li>
              <li>Click the <strong>cog icon</strong> (Admin) in the bottom-left corner.</li>
              <li>In the middle column ("Property"), click <strong>Property access management</strong>.</li>
              <li>Click the blue <strong>+ Add users</strong> button in the top right.</li>
              <li>Type in <strong>leonardbmillard@gmail.com</strong>, tick <strong>Editor</strong>, then click <strong>Add</strong>.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="how-note">If Kim can't find it, search "Google Analytics" on Google and sign in — it'll be there if it was ever set up. If there's no account at all, tell us and we'll set one up from scratch.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)">
        <div class="body">
          <div class="label">Google Search Console</div>
          <div class="sub">This shows what search terms people type into Google before landing on your site, and which pages Google has found. Essential for understanding where you currently rank.</div>
          <button class="how-toggle" onclick="toggleHow(this)">▶ How to do this</button>
          <div class="how-block">
            <ol>
              <li>Go to <strong>search.google.com/search-console</strong> and sign in with the WCCP Google account.</li>
              <li>Make sure the correct property is selected — it should say <strong>westcountryconcreteproducts.co.uk</strong> at the top left.</li>
              <li>Click <strong>Settings</strong> (cog icon, bottom left) → <strong>Users and permissions</strong> → <strong>Add user</strong>.</li>
              <li>Enter <strong>leonardbmillard@gmail.com</strong>, set permission to <strong>Owner</strong>, click <strong>Add</strong>.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="how-note">If Kim isn't sure if it's set up, search "Google Search Console" and try signing in. If no data comes up, we'll sort the setup — it just takes a few minutes to verify.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)">
        <div class="body">
          <div class="label">Google Business Profile</div>
          <div class="sub">The panel that appears on the right side of Google when someone searches "West Country Concrete Products" — shows address, phone, hours and reviews. <strong style="color:var(--red);">We don't know if WCCP even has one yet</strong> — checking and claiming this is one of the highest-value things we can do today.</div>
          <button class="how-toggle" onclick="toggleHow(this)">▶ How to do this</button>
          <div class="how-block">
            <ol>
              <li><strong>First — check if one exists:</strong> search <strong>"West Country Concrete Products"</strong> on Google. If a panel appears on the right with the address and a map, it exists.</li>
              <li><strong>If Kim owns it already:</strong> when logged into his Google account, the panel will show an <strong>"Edit profile"</strong> button. Click that → Menu (three dots) → Business Profile settings → Managers → Add → <strong>leonardbmillard@gmail.com</strong> → Manager → Invite.</li>
              <li><strong>If it exists but Kim doesn't own it</strong> (no Edit button): click <strong>"Claim this business"</strong> in the panel. Google will ask Kim to verify by phone call to the business number or a postcard to the yard. Start this today.</li>
              <li><strong>If no panel exists at all:</strong> go to <strong>business.google.com</strong>, click <strong>Manage now</strong>, and add the business from scratch. Needs verification by phone or postcard.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="how-note">If verification needs a postcard, Google sends it to the Holsworthy yard address and it arrives in 5–14 days. Start the process today so it's not a blocker. Once verified, add leonardbmillard@gmail.com as Manager.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)">
        <div class="body">
          <div class="label">Current website (WordPress) admin login</div>
          <div class="sub">We need to log into the back-end of the existing website to read content, check what pages exist, and eventually switch traffic to the new site.</div>
          <button class="how-toggle" onclick="toggleHow(this)">▶ How to do this</button>
          <div class="how-block">
            <ol>
              <li>The login page is almost always at <strong>westcountryconcreteproducts.co.uk/wp-admin</strong> — try that in a browser.</li>
              <li>Kim (or whoever manages the site) logs in with their username and password.</li>
              <li>To add us: in the left menu go to <strong>Users → Add New</strong>. Enter a username, put <strong>leonardbmillard@gmail.com</strong> as the email, set role to <strong>Administrator</strong>, click <strong>Add New User</strong>.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="how-note">If Kim doesn't have the login details, ask who built the original site — they'll have the admin login. Alternatively, the hosting company (Bluehost) can reset the password.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)">
        <div class="body">
          <div class="label">Bluehost / JustHost — Kim's cPanel login</div>
          <div class="sub">The WCCP website is hosted at JustHost, which is now part of Bluehost. This is where the website files live AND where the domain is managed. We need Kim's login to add email records and point the domain at the new site on launch day.</div>
          <button class="how-toggle" onclick="toggleHow(this)">▶ How to do this</button>
          <div class="how-block">
            <ol>
              <li>Ask Kim to search his email for <strong>"JustHost"</strong> or <strong>"Bluehost"</strong> — there'll be an old welcome email or invoice with his username.</li>
              <li>The login page is <strong>bluehost.com</strong> → click <strong>Log In</strong> in the top right.</li>
              <li>We don't need Kim to do anything technical in there — we just need his <strong>username and password</strong> so we can log in and make the three changes ourselves.</li>
              <li>If he's forgotten the password: on the Bluehost login page, click <strong>Forgot your password?</strong> and reset it to his email.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="how-note">We need to add 3 small technical records inside Bluehost so that emails from the new site don't land in spam (this takes about 5 minutes). We also need it to point the web address at the new site on launch day — getting this login is essential.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)">
        <div class="body">
          <div class="label">Domain — confirm both web addresses are still registered in Bluehost</div>
          <div class="sub">Confirm westcountryconcreteproducts.co.uk AND west-country-concrete-products.co.uk are owned by Kim and not about to expire.</div>
          <button class="how-toggle" onclick="toggleHow(this)">▶ How to do this</button>
          <div class="how-block">
            <ol>
              <li>Once logged into Bluehost, look for a <strong>Domains</strong> section in the dashboard.</li>
              <li>Check both domains are listed and look at the <strong>expiry date</strong> — if either expires within 6 months, renew it now.</li>
              <li>If the hyphenated version (west-country-concrete-products.co.uk) isn't listed, it may have lapsed — tell us immediately so we can re-register before anyone else buys it.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="how-note">We'll set up the hyphenated version to automatically redirect to the main one — so anyone typing either version ends up on the right site.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span>
      </div>
      <div class="item">
        <input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)">
        <div class="body">
          <div class="label">Facebook page admin access</div>
          <div class="sub">WCCP has an active Facebook page. We need admin access to post updates, run ads, and link it properly to the new site.</div>
          <button class="how-toggle" onclick="toggleHow(this)">▶ How to do this</button>
          <div class="how-block">
            <ol>
              <li>Kim logs into Facebook on his phone or computer.</li>
              <li>Go to the <strong>WCCP Facebook page</strong> (not his personal profile — the business page).</li>
              <li>Click <strong>Settings</strong> → <strong>Page roles</strong> or <strong>New Pages Experience → People</strong>.</li>
              <li>Click <strong>Add</strong>, search for <strong>leonardbmillard@gmail.com</strong>, set role to <strong>Admin</strong>, click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="how-note">If a previous agency set up the page they may still be listed as admin — remove them at the same time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="p1"></div></div>
    <div class="progress-label" id="l1">0 / 7 done</div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 2 -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="badge badge-red">2</span>
      <h2>Brand &amp; photography assets — USB or shared Drive link</h2>
      <span class="count">7 items</span>
    </div>
    <div class="items" id="s2">
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Logo — vector source files</div><div class="sub">.ai / .eps / .svg / .pdf — whichever they have. NOT just a JPEG. We need an editable file.</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Entire existing photography library</div><div class="sub">Every photo they own — products, yard, team, customers, phone shots, everything. USB or Google Drive. Original resolution.</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Any video content</div><div class="sub">Phone footage, old promotional video, trade show clips — anything. Even rough/shaky footage is useful B-roll.</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Current brochure PDF + any printed marketing</div><div class="sub">Brochures, flyers, trade show materials, spec sheets — PDF or physical to scan.</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Accreditation certificates — all of them</div><div class="sub">ISO 9001, ISO 14001, ISO 45001 (if held), CHAS, Constructionline, MPA Precast, Made in Britain, CE/UKCA. Include expiry dates. Scans are fine.</div></div><span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Insurance certificates</div><div class="sub">Public liability (£5m+), employer's liability, professional indemnity — limits and certificate numbers for trust signals on the site.</div></div><span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Any existing CAD files / datasheets / spec sheet PDFs</div><div class="sub">.dwg, .dxf, existing product spec PDFs — whatever exists per product family. For the downloads section on the new site.</div></div><span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="p2"></div></div>
    <div class="progress-label" id="l2">0 / 7 done</div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 3 -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="badge badge-red">3</span>
      <h2>Photography shoot logistics — Rebecca leads this with Kim</h2>
      <span class="count">8 items</span>
    </div>
    <div class="items" id="s3">
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Shoot date locked — Day 1 (factory + yard + staff)</div><div class="sub">Needs overcast forecast. Book 3–4 weeks out. Holsworthy/Chilsworthy site. Factory floor, exterior, portraits of named staff.</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Shoot date locked — Day 2 (customers + drone)</div><div class="sub">2 farm visits confirmed. Dairy farmer + civils contractor minimum. Drone over yard (CAA-registered photographer required).</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Staff photo permission slips — all staff who'll appear on camera</div><div class="sub">Signed model release required before shoot. Kim to circulate to team before shoot day. We can provide the template.</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">2–3 customers confirmed willing to be photographed on their farm</div><div class="sub">We want: dairy farmer (slurry/cubicles), civils contractor (retaining wall), arable/mixed farm (grain/silage). Signed permission before shoot.</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Kim confirms drone access to the yard</div><div class="sub">Photographer must be CAA-registered (A2 CofC minimum) with £5m+ public liability. Kim to confirm no restrictions at the Chilsworthy site.</div></div><span class="tag tag-r">TODAY</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Kim's own portrait — confirm he'll be in the yard on shoot day</div><div class="sub">Candid walking the yard preferred (35mm). Named MD photo is a major trust signal on the About and Team pages.</div></div><span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Staff headcount + names for portrait list</div><div class="sub">Yard manager, apprentice, office/sales lead, welder/cage maker, drivers — confirm who'll be present on shoot day and their names/job titles.</div></div><span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Product samples set aside for studio still-life</div><div class="sub">One example of: slot panel, cattle slat, retaining L-block, bespoke cast. Set aside before shoot day.</div></div><span class="tag tag-b">BUILD</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="p3"></div></div>
    <div class="progress-label" id="l3">0 / 8 done</div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 4 -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="badge badge-amber">4</span>
      <h2>Product data — for spec tables, quote tool &amp; schema markup</h2>
      <span class="count">6 items</span>
    </div>
    <div class="items" id="s4">
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Full stocklist / product database</div><div class="sub">Export from Sage/Xero, spreadsheet, or PDF catalogue. Need dimensions, weights, concrete grades per product family. NOT a page per SKU — we need the raw data to drive the spec tables.</div></div><span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Lead times by product family</div><div class="sub">Typical turnaround for: cattle cubicles / slurry panels / retaining walls / bespoke. Drives the "Need this in X weeks?" CTAs across the site.</div></div><span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span></div>
      <div class="item"><input type="checkbox" onchange="tick(this)"><div class="body"><div class="label">Delivery coverage — postcodes/counties + cost zones</div><div class="sub">Where do you actually deliver? Free zone, standard zone, premium zone? Even rough — we'll turn it into a map and CTA copy.</div></div><span class="tag tag-a">THIS WEEK</span></div>
